         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nDuring our school years, we learn to name everything around us through words. As we advance in our studies, we realize that these words sometimes have more than one meaning. Depending on the family’s financial situation, if a person has the opportunity to continue studying, they may also discover that the meanings of words can change over time (<htcite0>).\n\nThis lack of knowledge can lead us to make various interpretation mistakes, which brings us to our first reflection:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "79ea767b-924d-43e3-9bea-a8195b536dde",
                     "text": "Sabino, Marilei A.",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2011",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: I Was Mistaken</b><br /><br />Have you ever used current knowledge to interpret events from the past and later realized you had misunderstood the text?<br /><br />Have you ever thought that a word you use every day might not have the same meaning it had thousands of years ago?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
